<title>UK: Greenalls sells U.S. hotels for 14 mln stg.</title>
<headline>Greenalls sells U.S. hotels for 14 mln stg.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-12-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Greenalls Group Plc said on Friday that it has sold its six hotels in the U.S. to the Shaner Hotel Group for 14.0 million stg in cash.</p>
<p>The UK pubs to off-licences group said in a statement that the book value of the hotels is 13.5 million and, after allowing for costs of disposal and settlement of contractual arrangements, the loss on disposal is 1.75 million.</p>
<p>Andrew Thomas, chairman and chief executive of Greenalls, said, &quot;It has long been our intention to sell these hotels as they do not form part of our core business.&quot;</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 4019</p>
